    <h2 id="food-fat">Why Food (Specifically Fat) Is Non-Negotiable</h2>

    <p>This is the single most important factor in CoQ10 effectiveness. Your intestinal wall cannot absorb CoQ10 efficiently without the presence of bile acids and dietary fat to form the micelles that carry it into circulation. This isn't a minor optimization — it's the difference between a supplement that works and one that does not.</p>

    <div class="callout">
      <p>A 2013 study in <em>Nutrition Research</em> compared CoQ10 bioavailability across different food matrices. Participants who took 100mg CoQ10 with 3 grams of dietary fat showed 2.4x higher plasma concentrations than those taking the same dose with less than 1 gram of fat. The researchers concluded that <strong>at least 3-5 grams of fat is needed to optimize CoQ10 absorption</strong>, and doses of 10+ grams maximize it.</p>
      <cite>Nutrition Research, 2013 — CoQ10 bioavailability with dietary fat</cite>
    </div>

