    <details class="fq"><summary>When is the best time to take CoQ10?</summary><p>Morning with your largest fat-containing meal. Absorption is up to 300% higher with dietary fat. Split doses above 200mg between breakfast and lunch.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Can I take CoQ10 at night?</summary><p>Yes, but morning is preferred. Some users experience mild alertness or vivid dreams at night. Better than skipping — just take with dinner if mornings don't work.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Should CoQ10 be taken with food?</summary><p>Yes, always with fat-containing food. Avocado, eggs, olive oil, nuts, or fatty fish all work. Even 5-10g of fat significantly improves absorption.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>How long before CoQ10 starts working?</summary><p>Blood levels peak at 5-8 hours after dosing. Clinical benefits appear at 2-12 weeks of consistent daily use. Statin muscle pain often improves within 30 days.</p></details>
